# Super Fund Research Reference

This rule provides context on the existing super fund research tool located at `research/super-research/`. This is a standalone Python/Streamlit project used for personal superannuation research. It is NOT part of the KhufusHome monorepo apps — it lives in the repo as a reference artifact only.

When building the finance dashboard (`apps/finance`), use this research as the domain knowledge source.

## What It Contains

### Data (CSV files in `research/super-research/data/`)

- **`returns/annual_returns.csv`** — Year-by-year fund returns (FY2016–FY2025) for all compared funds. After-investment-fees basis. Column: `fund_id, fy, return_pct, return_type, source`.
- **`returns/annualised_returns.csv`** — Annualised returns across 1yr/3yr/5yr/7yr/10yr periods. Column: `fund_id, period, return_pct, as_at, source`.
- **`allocations/asset_allocations.csv`** — Asset allocation breakdowns (AU equities, intl equities, property, infrastructure, private equity, alternatives, fixed income, cash).
- **`fees/fee_structures.csv`** — Fee structures per fund: admin flat fee, admin %, investment fee %, performance fee %, transaction costs, total on $50k/$100k.
- **`benchmarks/au_median_balance_by_age.csv`** — ATO median/average super balances by age group (male/female).

### Config (YAML files in `research/super-research/config/`)

- **`funds.yaml`** — Metadata for 10 funds: id, name, option, type (industry/retail), AUM, members, return target, growth/defensive split, website.
- **`personal.yaml`** — User's personal profile: age, balance, salary, SG rate, contribution history (7 snapshots Oct 2020–Mar 2026), assumptions.

### Research Papers (Markdown in `research/super-research/research/fund_papers/`)

Detailed research papers for each of the 10 compared funds covering performance, fees, asset allocation, strengths/weaknesses, and sources. Plus a `master_comparison.md` with the full cross-fund analysis.

